# API Generator — Flutter Base Template

> **Path note (2026-06-15):** All import paths in this rule reflect the new `foundation/platform/infra` structure.
> Core is now split: `core/foundation/` (pure Dart), `core/platform/` (Flutter/OS wrappers), `core/infra/` (implementation).
> See `readme/architecture.md` for the full layer map.

Generates complete Flutter code from a REST (OpenAPI) or GraphQL API with optional Figma UI support.
See `readme/apigenerator.md`, `readme/architecture.md`, `readme/pagination.md`, and `readme/scripts.md` for full documentation.

---

## 📋 Input Format

### REST API:
```
Feature: {feature_name}
Type: REST
APIs:
- GET /endpoint
- POST /endpoint/{id}

OpenAPI: https://your-api.com/openapi.json
Figma: https://figma.com/design/fileKey/fileName?node-id=1-2   ← optional
```

### GraphQL API — Case A: operation already generated:
```
Feature: {feature_name}
Type: GraphQL
Operations:
- Mutation: EmailLogin
- Query: GetAccountById

Figma: https://figma.com/design/fileKey/fileName?node-id=1-2   ← optional
```
> No URL needed. The endpoint is in `Env().config.baseUrl`.
> Generated files are in `lib/core/network/gql/config/documents/{mutations|queries}/generated/`.

---

### GraphQL API — Case B: operation NOT yet generated (new):
```
Feature: {feature_name}
Type: GraphQL
Operations:
- Mutation: CreateOrder
  definition: |
    mutation CreateOrder($input: CreateOrderInput!) {
      createOrder(input: $input) {
        id
        status
        total
      }
    }

Figma: https://figma.com/design/fileKey/fileName?node-id=1-2   ← optional
```

When `definition` is provided, the flow is:
1. Create `lib/core/network/gql/config/documents/mutations/create_order.graphql` with the definition
2. Run `dart run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs` to generate `create_order.graphql.dart`
3. Then proceed with the full feature generation using the generated file

