## ❄️ FREEZED — Required for ALL States

### Golden Rule
**Every State in the project uses `@freezed`. No exceptions.**

### Cubit file structure
```dart
// {name}_cubit.dart
import 'package:freezed_annotation/freezed_annotation.dart';
import 'package:flutter_bloc/flutter_bloc.dart';
import 'package:injectable/injectable.dart';

part '{name}_cubit.freezed.dart';   // ← required
part '{name}_state.dart';            // ← required

@injectable
class {Name}Cubit extends Cubit<{Name}State> {
  {Name}Cubit(...) : super(const {Name}State.initial());
  ...
}
```

### State file structure
```dart
// {name}_state.dart
part of '{name}_cubit.dart';

@freezed
abstract class {Name}State with _${Name}State {
  const factory {Name}State.initial()                            = {Name}Initial;
  const factory {Name}State.loading()                            = {Name}Loading;
  const factory {Name}State.loaded()                             = {Name}Loaded;
  const factory {Name}State.error({required String errorMessage}) = {Name}Error;
}
```

### Consuming State in the Screen
```dart
// BlocConsumer for states with side effects (e.g. toast on error)
BlocConsumer<{Name}Cubit, {Name}State>(
  listener: (context, state) {
    state.maybeWhen(
      error: (msg) => context.showToast(
        type: EnumTost.error,
        description: msg,
      ),
      orElse: () {},
    );
  },
  builder: (context, state) {
    return state.when(
      initial: () => const SizedBox.shrink(),
      loading: () => const LoadingWidget(),
      loaded: () => const {Name}Body(),
      error: (_) => const SizedBox.shrink(),
    );
  },
)
```

> **Note:** Cubits that extend `PaginationCubit<E>` do NOT need a state file — `PaginationCubit` manages all states internally with freezed.

