## 🔷 GraphQL API — Complete Flow

> Use this section when `Type: GraphQL` is specified. GraphQL uses `GQLService` instead of `ApiService`, and `CancelInstance` instead of `CancelToken`.

### Key Differences: REST vs GraphQL

| | REST | GraphQL |
|---|---|---|
| Service | `ApiService` (Retrofit/Dio) | `GQLService` |
| Cancel token | `CancelToken` (Dio) | `CancelInstance` |
| Schema source | OpenAPI URL | Generated `.graphql.dart` files |
| Data model | Manual `fromJson` model | Generated classes (`Options$`, `Variables$`, `Input$`) |
| Repository returns | `Either<Failure, Entity>` | `Either<Failure, Entity>` (same) |
| Error handling | `on DioException` | check `res?.success`, `res?.errorMessage` |
| UseCase base | `BaseUseCase<Result, Params>` | `BaseUseCase<Result, Params>` (same) |

### GQL DataSource (Mutation example — EmailLogin)
```dart
// lib/Features/{feature}/data/datasources/{feature}_remote_datasource.dart
import 'package:flutter_base_template/core/network/gql/cancel_instance.dart';
import 'package:flutter_base_template/core/network/gql/config/documents/mutations/generated/{name}.graphql.dart';
import 'package:flutter_base_template/core/network/gql/config/generated/schema.graphql.dart';
import 'package:flutter_base_template/core/network/gql/gql_service.dart';
import 'package:flutter_base_template/Features/{feature}/data/datasources/{feature}_local_datasource.dart';
import 'package:graphql_flutter/graphql_flutter.dart';
import 'package:injectable/injectable.dart';

@singleton
class {Feature}RemoteDataSource {
  final GQLService _gqlService;
  final {Feature}LocalDatasource _localDatasource;  // for extra inputs like FCM token

  {Feature}RemoteDataSource(this._gqlService, this._localDatasource);

  // Mutation example
  Future<QueryResult?>? {operationName}({
    required String field1,
    required String field2,
    required String languageCode,   // always passed from UseCase via context
    CancelInstance? cancelToken,
  }) {
    return _gqlService.mutate(
      cancel: cancelToken,
      Options$Mutation${OperationName}(
        variables: Variables$Mutation${OperationName}(
          {inputName}: Input${InputTypeName}(
            field1: field1,
            field2: field2,
            deviceToken: _localDatasource.getFcm(),  // if needed
            languageCode: languageCode,
          ),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }

  // Query example
  Future<QueryResult?>? get{Name}({
    required String param,
    CancelInstance? cancelToken,
  }) {
    return _gqlService.query(
      cancel: cancelToken,
      Options$Query${OperationName}(
        variables: Variables$Query${OperationName}(param: param),
      ),
    );
  }
}
```

### GQL Repository Abstract (Domain)
```dart
// lib/Features/{feature}/domain/repositories/{feature}_repository.dart
abstract class {Feature}Repository {
  Future<Either<Failure, {Entity}>> {methodName}({
    required String field1,
    required String field2,
    required String languageCode,
    CancelInstance? cancelToken,
