### GQL Repository Implementation
```dart
// lib/Features/{feature}/data/repositories/{feature}_repository_impl.dart
import 'package:dartz/dartz.dart';
import 'package:flutter_base_template/core/network/gql/cancel_instance.dart';
import 'package:flutter_base_template/core/network/gql/gql_service.dart';   // 🚨 REQUIRED for QueryResultExt
import 'package:flutter_base_template/core/foundation/errors/failure.dart';
import 'package:flutter_base_template/Features/{feature}/data/datasources/{feature}_remote_datasource.dart';
import 'package:flutter_base_template/Features/{feature}/data/models/{name}_model.dart';
import 'package:flutter_base_template/Features/{feature}/domain/entities/{entity}.dart';
import 'package:flutter_base_template/Features/{feature}/domain/params/{name}_params.dart';
import 'package:flutter_base_template/Features/{feature}/domain/repositories/{feature}_repository.dart';
// For Mutation: import the generated mutation file
import 'package:flutter_base_template/core/network/gql/config/documents/mutations/generated/{name}.graphql.dart';
// For Query: import the generated query file
// import 'package:flutter_base_template/core/network/gql/config/documents/queries/generated/{name}.graphql.dart';
import 'package:graphql_flutter/graphql_flutter.dart';
import 'package:injectable/injectable.dart';

@LazySingleton(as: {Feature}Repository)
class {Feature}RepositoryImpl implements {Feature}Repository {
  final {Feature}RemoteDataSource _remoteDataSource;
  {Feature}RepositoryImpl(this._remoteDataSource);

  @override
  Future<Either<Failure, {Entity}>> {methodName}({
    required {Name}Params params,
    CancelInstance? cancelToken,
  }) async {
    try {
      final res = await _remoteDataSource.{methodName}(
        params: params,
        cancelToken: cancelToken,
      );
      if (res != null && res.success) {
        // ✅ Parse the full typed response using the generated fromJson constructor
        // For Mutation:  Mutation${OperationName}.fromJson(res.data as Map<String, dynamic>)
        // For Query:     Query${OperationName}.fromJson(res.data as Map<String, dynamic>)
        final parsed = Mutation${OperationName}.fromJson(
          res.data as Map<String, dynamic>,
        );
        // ✅ Map generated type → model → entity  (fromGql + toEntity)
        return Right({Name}Model.fromGql(parsed.{operationNameCamelCase}).toEntity());
      } else {
        return Left(UnexpectedFailure(message: res?.errorMessage ?? 'Unknown error'));
      }
    } on GraphQLError catch (e) {
      return Left(UnexpectedFailure(message: e.message));
    }
  }
}
```

> ⚠️ **`res.success` and `res.errorMessage`** are extension getters defined in `gql_service.dart` (`QueryResultExt`).
> 🚨 **ALWAYS import `gql_service.dart` in the GQL repository impl** — without it, `res.success` and `res.errorMessage` will throw "getter not defined" compile errors:
> ```dart
> import 'package:flutter_base_template/core/network/gql/gql_service.dart'; // required for QueryResultExt
> ```
>
> 🚨 **NEVER access `res.data!['key']['field']` directly** — always use the generated `fromJson` constructor to parse the typed response, then `fromGql().toEntity()` to get the domain entity.

### GQL UseCase
```dart
// lib/Features/{feature}/domain/usecases/{use_case}.dart
import 'package:flutter_base_template/core/di/injection.dart';
import 'package:flutter_base_template/core/network/gql/cancel_instance.dart';
import 'package:flutter_base_template/core/foundation/domain/base_usecase.dart';
import 'package:flutter_base_template/routes/router.dart';
import 'package:easy_localization/easy_localization.dart';
import 'package:injectable/injectable.dart';

@injectable
class {UseCaseName} extends BaseUseCase<Either<Failure, {Entity}>, {Params}> {
  {UseCaseName}(this._{featureRepository});
  final {Feature}Repository _{featureRepository};

  @override
  Future<Either<Failure, {Entity}>> call(covariant {Params} params) async {
    final result = await _{featureRepository}.{methodName}(
      field1: params.field1,
      field2: params.field2,
      // ✅ languageCode is read here from context — NOT in DataSource or Repository
      languageCode: getIt<AppRouter>().navigatorKey.currentContext!.locale.languageCode,
      cancelToken: resetCancelToken(true) as CancelInstance?,  // true = GQL
    );
    // Add any post-success side effects here (e.g. saving token)
    result.fold((_) {}, (entity) { /* e.g. save token */ });
    return result;
  }
}
```

> **`resetCancelToken(bool isGQL)`** — pass `true` for GQL (`CancelInstance`), `false` for REST (`CancelToken`).
> **`languageCode` rule:** Always read from context **in the UseCase**, never in DataSource or Repository.

### GQL DI Registration
```dart
// GQLService depends on AuthLocalDatasource (NOT AuthRepository — to avoid circular deps)
gh.lazySingleton<GQLService>(
  () => GQLService(gh<AuthLocalDatasource>()));

// DataSource needs GQLService + LocalDatasource
gh.singleton<{Feature}RemoteDataSource>(
  () => {Feature}RemoteDataSource(
    gh<GQLService>(),
    gh<{Feature}LocalDatasource>(),
  ));

// Repository
gh.lazySingleton<{Feature}Repository>(
  () => {Feature}RepositoryImpl(gh<{Feature}RemoteDataSource>()));

// UseCase
gh.factory<{UseCaseName}>(
  () => {UseCaseName}(gh<{Feature}Repository>()));

// Cubit
gh.factory<{Name}Cubit>(
  () => {Name}Cubit(gh<{UseCaseName}>()));
```

> ⚠️ **Circular dependency rule:** `GQLService` must depend on `AuthLocalDatasource`, NOT `AuthRepository`.
> Chain: `AuthRemoteDataSource → GQLService → AuthLocalDatasource` ✅
> Chain: `AuthRemoteDataSource → GQLService → AuthRepository → AuthRemoteDataSource` ❌

### CancelInstance vs CancelToken

| | REST | GraphQL |
|---|---|---|
| Class | `CancelToken` (from `dio`) | `CancelInstance` (from `core/network/gql/cancel_instance.dart`) |
| `BaseUseCase.resetCancelToken` | `resetCancelToken(false)` | `resetCancelToken(true)` |
| Cast | `as CancelToken?` | `as CancelInstance?` |
| Cancel check | `token.isCancelled` | `instance.isCanceled` |

### GQLService Utility Methods

After login or locale change you **must** call one of these to keep GraphQL requests authenticated and correctly localised:

```dart
final gqlService = getIt<GQLService>();

// ✅ After successful login — updates token + locale header + reinitialises client
await gqlService.initWithIso();
// or: only update the Bearer token (lighter — no locale refresh)
gqlService.setToken(token);   // pass null to remove (on logout)

// ✅ After app locale changes
gqlService.setLanguage(newLocale.languageCode);

// ✅ On logout — remove the auth header
gqlService.setToken(null);
```

> ⚠️ **GQLService uses a static header map** — it is initialized once in the constructor.
> After login, REST API picks up the token automatically (via `AuthInterceptor`), but **GQL does NOT**.
> You must call `gqlService.setToken(token)` or `gqlService.initWithIso()` inside the login UseCase after a successful GQL or REST login to ensure authenticated GQL calls work.

