## 💉 Dependency Injection

```bash
# After creating files, run:
dart run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs
```

### REST — Registration order
```dart
// 1. DataSource
gh.singleton<{Feature}RemoteDataSource>(
  () => {Feature}RemoteDataSource(gh<{Feature}ApiService>()));

// 2. Repository registered as abstract type
gh.lazySingleton<{Feature}Repository>(
  () => {Feature}RepositoryImpl(gh<{Feature}RemoteDataSource>()));

// 3. Use Case
gh.factory<{UseCaseName}>(
  () => {UseCaseName}(gh<{Feature}Repository>()));

// 4. Cubit
gh.factory<{Name}Cubit>(
  () => {Name}Cubit(gh<{UseCaseName}>()));
```

### GraphQL — Registration order
```dart
// 0. GQLService (depends on AuthLocalDatasource — NOT AuthRepository)
gh.lazySingleton<GQLService>(
  () => GQLService(gh<AuthLocalDatasource>()));

// 1. DataSource (needs GQLService + LocalDatasource)
gh.singleton<{Feature}RemoteDataSource>(
  () => {Feature}RemoteDataSource(
    gh<GQLService>(),
    gh<{Feature}LocalDatasource>(),
  ));

// 2. Repository
gh.lazySingleton<{Feature}Repository>(
  () => {Feature}RepositoryImpl(gh<{Feature}RemoteDataSource>()));

// 3. UseCase
gh.factory<{UseCaseName}>(
  () => {UseCaseName}(gh<{Feature}Repository>()));

// 4. Cubit
gh.factory<{Name}Cubit>(
  () => {Name}Cubit(gh<{UseCaseName}>()));
```

**Rules:**
- ✅ Register repository as abstract type: `gh.lazySingleton<AbstractRepo>(() => ImplRepo(...))`
- ✅ `@LazySingleton` for stateless repos (users, products)
- ✅ `@Singleton` for stateful repos (auth with tokens)
- ✅ `@injectable` (factory) for Use Cases and Cubits
- ✅ `GQLService` depends on `AuthLocalDatasource` (NOT `AuthRepository`) — avoids circular dependency
- ❌ Never register the concrete implementation type directly

**Exception — Cubit without UseCase:**
```dart
// Only when there is no API call (local storage only)
// Example: SplashCubit checks for a saved token
@injectable
class SplashCubit extends Cubit<SplashState> {
  SplashCubit(this._authRepository) : super(const SplashState.initial());
  final AuthRepository _authRepository;  // ← abstract type directly

  void loadResources() {
    final hasToken = _authRepository.getTokenUser();
    emit(hasToken ? const SplashState.loadedWithAuth() : const SplashState.loaded());
  }
}
```

